(power_internal, power_logic).explanation: Power_logic is a component that contributes to the total internal power consumption of a processor, as logic circuits are a fundamental part of internal power dissipation;

(power_internal, area_cell_area).explanation: The cell area of a processor design influences internal power consumption because larger cell areas typically result in higher power dissipation due to increased capacitance and switching activity;

(power_internal, power_register).explanation: Power_register represents the power consumed by register files and contributes directly to the total internal power consumption of the processor;
